result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
NO RECORD MADE. Attorney Emily K. Gaertner in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Joseph Corcoran in court for Jamie L. Turner. Defendant Jamie L. Turner in court. Clerk. M.Burke. State in victim rights compliance. Parties are working on a resolution.
Status conference scheduled for November 17, 2022 at 10:30 am.

Defendant, Jamie L. Turner, appeared with Attorney Joseph Corcoran.  Attorney Rosa Delgado appeared for the Prosecution.  Clerk JT  Minutes: DE motion to dismiss; arguments heard; Court denies motion.    ST called witness KSD Dep Keith Kirwan; sworn in and testified; cross-examination by Atty Corcoran. ST rested and moved for bind over; arguments heard. Probable cause found; bound over for trial. Information filed; reading waived. Not guilty pleas entered. Scheduling Order given to Attorney in court.   Bond continued.  Judicial Pretrial - in court scheduled for October 7, 2022 at 09:30 am.

records.addlTxt: Attorney Thomas Binger appeared for the State.  Defendant in custody and appeared in court w/ Attorney Corcoran.  Clerk. M.Burke. Attorney Corcoran advises that the DE states she is competent. Case is unsuspended and Court finds DE competent to proceed. PH set to 08/25/22 at 8:15.
Due to the DE being transported to KCDC the CH of 08/17/22 at 9:30 has been set to 08/15/22 at 3:30.

The Court Liaison from Mendota requested a Writ be prepared for the DE to appear at the competency hearing. Due to needing more time for a writ to be prepared and transportation to be done the CH of 08/10/22 at 9:30 has been reset to 08/17/22 at 9:30.

records.descr: DE not competent to stand trial, case suspended

records.addlTxt: Attorney Emily Gaertner appeared for the State.  Defendant in custody and appeared by zoom w/ Attorney Corcoran.   Clerk. M.Burke. Atty Corcoran states that the DE indicates she believes she is incompetenct but agrees with that she is likely to regain competency. Court finds DE incompetent. Case suspended. Court orders same treatment as previously ordered. Bond motion will be heard when case is unsuspended.
With Jennifer/Mendota Mental Health Institute a zoom appearance has been arranged for the HE on 06/01/22 at 11:30.
